# BookLens project rules

- Keep the first build small: data pipeline, Next.js UI, top tags, and similar-books recommendations.
- Do not add FastAPI/Modal until a separate backend/API is actually needed.
- Do not add Supabase until auth, database, or storage is actually needed.
- Do not add LiteLLM or provider SDKs until model calls are actually needed.
- Work inside WSL2 Ubuntu, not under `/mnt/c/...`.
- Use Linux-side Node, npm, Python, uv, git, and make.
- Never commit `.env` files, API keys, service-role keys, database URLs, deployment credentials, or model provider keys.
- Commit only `.env.example` files with placeholder variable names.
